description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a part time (22.5 hours), band 3 physiotherapy assistant post within Trauma &amp; Orthopaedic Physiotherapy team.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidate will join a friendly team of physiotherapists and physiotherapy assistants working across the T&amp;O unit within SBU. You will be based at Morriston &amp; Neath Hospitals, although some community work may be required at times.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;There will be an expectation for you to participate in additional weekend services.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The current team works closely with the wider MDT to promote rehabilitation and independence for the T&amp;O patients.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are a friendly, inclusive and fair team and are looking for someone who embraces and promotes these values.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The role would require you to work both collaboratively and independently, using protocol lead treatments, to assist the Physiotherapists in delivering patient centred, quality care across both the elective and trauma wards as well as helping in educational sessions for patients and carers. There are elements of both clinical and clerical work and computer confidence would be an advantage.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further information please contact:-&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Sharon Maggs&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Clinical Team Lead T&amp;O&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
